id: pm-6ef3
title: "ADR: Extension sandbox profiles are advisory governance attestations, not enforced isolation"
description: "Extension sandbox profiles are advisory governance attestations, not enforced isolation"
type: Decision
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: adr,architecture,"area:extensions",security
created_at: "2026-05-31T19:47:45.328Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-31T20:26:00.874Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-m2u1
resolution: Accepted ADR recorded in living map
expected_result: "The ADR captures a durable architecture or operating decision with context, consequences, and evidence for future agents."
actual_result: "The closed Decision 'ADR: Extension sandbox profiles are advisory governance attestations, not enforced isolation' is recorded under the ADR living log and preserved as durable project context."
close_reason: ADR recorded and accepted; architectural decision documented as durable context on 2026-05-31.
body: "CONTEXT: manifests declare sandbox_profile none|restricted|strict, but extensions run in-process with full Node access. DECISION: in v0.x, profiles are a policy/attestation surface only (no vm/Worker/seccomp) because ESM+native-addon vm isolation is incomplete and the primary consumers are trusted; coarse protection comes from trust_mode=enforce + require_provenance. CONSEQUENCES: zero activation overhead, full API for extensions; an untrusted malicious extension is not contained by profile alone; should surface an advisory warning (proposed) clarifying the guarantee. EVIDENCE: src/core/extensions/extension-policy.ts, loader.ts import(); item pm-7sd."
